
Overview of verb aggravate

The verb aggravate has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (3) worsen, aggravate, exacerbate, exasperate -- (make worse; "This drug aggravates the pain")
2. (2) exacerbate, exasperate, aggravate -- (exasperate or irritate)

Overview of adj aggravated

The adj aggravated has 2 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                    
1. aggravated -- (made more severe or intense especially in law; "aggravated assault")
2. aggravated, provoked -- (incited, especially deliberately, to anger; "aggravated by passive resistance"; "the provoked animal attacked the child")
